\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 My name, May Stuart Martin, Stuart with a U.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 And this address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 This is 9 St Andrew Street, Darlington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Are you a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Can you tell me the year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I'll do sums first. That'll be 1938.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 And the year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 And where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 In Gateshead. I think it was 99 High Park Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It - it must have been a very short time because - we went to Newcastle, and my brother who was two years and
 two months younger than myself was born in Water Terrace, Newcastle. And we lived at 11 Tunstall Terrace - yes, 11 - no that's my grandfather's address, 11 Tamworth Road, that's the first house I remember living in That was in Newcastle. Yes. And I must 
have been - five - between five and six when we came back to Gateshead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 We lived at - in - I never knew whether to say Teviot or Teviot Street, 20 - 20, we always said Teviot Street but I have a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465  lurking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  suspicion that was wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh a good while, I must have been about - fourteen I think by the time we left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 That's 1919, the end of our period isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So that was the house you lived in most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember why the family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't really know. Mother used to make rather a joke about having moved so often. I didn't - I didn't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was it anything to do with your father's job perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When we went to Newcastle it might have been for him to be nearer because he worked in Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well in the end there were four of us but we were well spaced out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could you give me the spacing, who was the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I was the eldest myself. I had a - a brother, two years and two months younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 He was Robert. And in 1918, that's - another eleven years after my brother I had a sister, she was a war baby you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 She was Edith Lesley. And five years later there was a - another brother. John Albert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born or could you perhaps tell me his date of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, he was born at 20th of March 1884.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Sunderland.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 He was in the Post Office as a sorter. Part of the time during this period he was on the mail train between Newcastle and Birmingham.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Still sorting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Yes, he was on shift work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Have you any idea when that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What years would he be on the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I should think it would cover quite a lot of the period from - perhaps I might be about five year old up to - ten or s
o, afterwards he came back and went into the - parcels office at Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he have another job before he became a sorter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Or any jobs after he became a Post Office sorter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well of course he was promoted be - later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - well I suppose there were gradual steps in promotion but - he died when he was only forty-nine - by then he was a - an overseer. Still in the parcels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But in 1911 he'd just be an ordinary sorter would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, they were quite poor then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You can't remember the date when he became an overseer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh, it would be well - well on. Yes. 'Cos he went to the war you see, in between too. He - he - he joined right at the beginning in 1914. And - he
 was - quite badly wounded in 1916, had this right arm broken and they set thirteen different places, so he was in hospital really for years. And - and had - not scores but - up to about twenty different operations and they did save his arm for him which 
was considered rather - special. So that took a lot of time out of his working life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It would make it hard for you too, or did the Army help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh there was a separation allowance as we called it and I suppose there'd be something for the two youn
g children. But it wouldn't be easy at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever do any casual or part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - now I couldn't tell you about the date but in due course he - he did become the local - organizer for the Union Of Post Office Workers, which I 
think was just starting then. And - I don't - I never heard of any pay that he would get for it but there was a - a very large clumsy typewriter that came into the house. In connection with those duties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You've no idea about when that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, now - oh I think it - it must have been - this goes up to 19 - I think it could have been later than 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, he wasn't out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How old was your mother when you were born, or do you know her date of birth, or whether she was younger or older than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 She was six months older than my father, she was born on the 21st September 1883.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 She came - at the time she had come from Sunderlan
d but she had more of a - she must have had a - a wandering childhood even, must have - she must have been the one who wanted to keep moving, she had lived at Wallsend, she had lived in Newcastle, she went to Gillingham Road school which was proud of. She
 
had lived in Sunderland, she had lived - I think as a child in Hartlepool, I know my grandmother came from Hartlepool, but they weren't big moves but - I - I'm not quite sure, she - she had just come from Sunderland when they were married but I think orig
inally she would come from Hartlepool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Had your mother any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 She was in domestic service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she work after she was married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What particular job did she do in domestic service, general work or specialized?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I think it was mostly housemaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 The house at Gateshead was 20 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Teviot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. That's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many rooms were in the house at Teviot Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Now there'd be five rooms, three bedrooms, sitting room, livi
ng room and a - a bathroom and a - a separate toilet which - sounds quite good, there wasn't any separate scullery. It was only eight shillings a week rent. I expect that seemed a lot at first but - all the time we were there they always - mentioned the e
ight shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Just the odd time, somebody might stay for a - night or two but - no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, not during that - period. A long time afterwards - she had a woman in once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But that was later on after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh it was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember wash day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, I do, it started with the old ponch tub you know and - the mangle, they didn't call it a wringer even it was a mangle. Was a little wash house at the top of the yard, it was a big yard with two steps in it. Bu
t - a long time afterwards - probably after the period we gravitated to a - a washing machine which was quite - something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes, did your mother make any clothes for you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. Practically nothing, she - she wasn't good with the needle I have to say, she didn't make like some people either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were the clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well it's - there - there were some secondhand ones that came in, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where would you get those from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - my - mother's sister was also in service and - she - I can remember, brought some things from the place where she was working. I can remember distinctly some - rather nice little blue - frocks, and it would be drill that I got, they were very p
lain but they did fit and - I rather liked them. She always - she bought pretty well everything at - at sales, sale price and looking back now I - I - well even then I realised they weren't suitable. They weren't the right size. And especially when I went
 to the secondary school - she couldn't see that I ought to have something like the other girls by way of uniform for gym and so on. I - I had some - some very peculiar clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I suppose for economy's sake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 That was it. Oh yes. There's no doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When you say she got them from sales, were they too big for you or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, but - that was part of the economy as well, you could - she must have things that - I - would last me for a long time as I was growing. So - that was 
how they were generally too big. Bit floppy. And - and old fashioned - well, I don't know. I've many bitter memories about some - what did we call them in those days, I think; they called them drawers, and - they were - a sort of butchers blue with a very
 
broad white stripe and a trap door at the back. Can you imagine? And - one day a - a few of us - were going to have a little trip to the seaside, we'd saved up, it never occurred to me that we would go what we called plodging then - paddling, and all the 
o
thers would tuck up their frocks and stick them inside their knickers and there was I with this - this terrible arrangement, and - and it also had a - great big - rather rough tucks in as well being too long, and I just had to try to laugh it off but I di
dn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 And where had she got those from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
From - a sale. They were new - they were - they were uncomfortably stiff, they were terribly - terribly new. And I didn't like those. But - well - I have to pay tribute to her, she didn't have much 
to work on and she was doing her best and of course she was pretty young really to - to have dealings with children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When you had new clothes that weren't from the sale do you remember where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - I can remember some of the names of the shops where we went. I think she rather liked Law and Moorhouses in Newcastle. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 And - I don't think we went ever to Fenwick's, we knew about Fenwick's but I don't remember ever buying anything there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
And the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have new clothes at any particular time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I think - when I was little I quite often had a new hat for Whit Sunday. There used to be the school - Sunday school anniversary and - had to say our pieces and we were supposed to have a - at first a white frock b
ut later on it didn't matter so much. But I don't remember getting a - a new frock but I generally had a new hat. With elastic on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother mend your clothes, was she able to sew to that extent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes - she did mend, it - what seemed all
 right to me but now - now I can see it - she didn't do it very well, and quite - quite early in - in my career the job of darning the socks came my way. We used to have the - the big basket without a handle and it somehow nearly always seemed to be full 
o
f socks. And I got the job that I had to mend the socks, darn the socks and the - quite big holes and you know you were soon mending on top of the old darns, because we - we used our things and used our things - until they were pretty well falling to piec
es.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father mend the shoes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, I can remember - yes, he did do some cobbling as they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were your shoes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - I think the shoes would be new. Actually they were boots you know in those days
. At first I had long - tall boots with laces all the way, used to take ages to fasten them. When I went to the secondary school they - we - got into the way of wearing boys boots which were just - above the ankle and - they were - better fitting really, 
they were broader, I always had broad feet. Had difficulty. And they were much - quicker and - well quite smart in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember where your shoes came from, your new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I think those would be Co-op mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have those at any particular time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think so - just - had to last as long as they could.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, did he help with the housework at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I can remember - being on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 shift work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  sometimes he was - at - at home during the day and - he did used to - help with the washing. I can't remember anything else that he helped with at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Cooking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When he helped with the washing what part would he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh some of the - turning the wringer, that seemed to be the bits that he liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever help with the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Or lighting the fires.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever do any decorating or repairs or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I don't remember him ever doing anything like that, but I - I suppose he must have done because it got done didn't it. I can remember mother - would - with the steps and - the - paste and the - the wallpaper, but I don't think she would do it by herself.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father ever help with the children, did he ever dress or undress you at all? Or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so. I can't remember that but - very rarely he would take us out. I can - I can remember, as a - it was a real treat if 
we were going out with daddy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever take you out without your mother, was that just on your own with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 There was - one time when a - a cousin was being born and - daddy got the job to look after us while mother went to see the n
ew arrival. And he took us to the - I think he took us to the pictures, but - you know, that seems a bit early for a film. Well she's five years younger than me, that's - that's going to be - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It would be more magic lantern things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. We w
ould - we did go - we had magic lantern things. I think that - I think we'd better not be quite positive about that but I have this - this idea he took us out and I thought it must have been to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever take you anywhere else without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I don't think so. But he - he got a - an allotment he would go and I had a garden, which was quite a distance from the house, later on he got one nearer, and it entailed a - a - big climb up what we called the Banky Fields to get back, '
cos we lived out - on the edge of the town and - it was rather a treat to go to the garden. And - went on Saturdays and got little jobs to do. Mostly - picking stones off the soil, but - we really thought that was a treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I can't remember that but - later on - when I was - well, I suppose - included in - before I was - thirteen and - and later, he used to try to talk to me to - to bring me out of - and things like politics and so on you know.
 I can't remember - about stories though as being - when I was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father, you 
said on Saturdays you helped at the allotment, did you help in the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes. Well it wasn't only Saturdays at the - allotment, I suppose in the summer it would be in the evenings as well. Yes - I can }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 distinctly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  remember that when I was - s
even years old they gave me a - a watch for my birthday and - also because I'd grown up now I was to - to help with washing the floors. And - ever - oh until I was grown up. I suppose I'd rather - it was - twenty - twenty-two or so there was still this - 
t
his weekly business of washing the floors and - when I was - earlier than that I used to clean the - the taps, all these - there used to be all these taps of - brass you know that had to be cleaned with metal polish. And - I was very little when I - I - I
 had that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you carry on doing the taps after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well no. No, I don't know how that came about. Maybe - maybe when we moved to another house - there weren't that kind of tap anymore that needed to be cleaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your brothers and sister have particular jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, they - they got off. Well you see they - they weren't - they weren't born in time are they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It would only be your brother wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. No, no, I was - I was always jealous of him, he 
was always - the favourite, and being a boy and being the younger he wasn't expected to do anything. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult, that would be after 1918 when the others were born wouldn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well I was - I was the older one and I had to - look after my brother a lot, I - I - yes, I was - I was the one that looked after the house while both mother and dad went out at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever help him with dressing or eating or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh yes, I expect so. I was only two years older but I was always - sort of - I suppose I - I was - after - be getting on to about - seven or so before I was trusted that much but it - my whole ideas that - one after another I was always lookin
g after - younger kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he help you in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. And he could listen in to the tape if he likes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes. I don't remember what time but - there - there was a set time and - the edict went forth you know, bedtime, and we had to go up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you know what time it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I should think seven o'clock when I was - quite young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - they would when we were little, I don't remember being put to bed but - for a while they used to come up to see that we were in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What age do you think you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I should think probably from about four or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you share a bedroom with anyone or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, my brother and I shared the bedroom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have separate beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You shared a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How long did you continue to share a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - I'm going to have to - I don't really know.
 I suppose they would get us into separate beds like when I was about ten and he about eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did the rest of the family sleep then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well mother and dad had a bedroom and - Bob and I had one then I - can't properly remember, but there was a 
little bedroom which - as far as I remember was a - a spare room you know for putting boxes and things, but in time that must have become - a separate room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have a fitted bath even in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What do you call a fitted bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I mean a proper bath attached to taps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. Yes, that was rather - a bit - was bit - the house was a peculiar shape. When - when you went in the front door there was a - sort of octagonal hall, and - on the right was t
he bathroom door, downstairs just in - just inside the front door. And you went through the bathroom to come to the toilet. It'd be a separate section but this was - an unusual kind of place to live, it was an unfinished housing estate. Somebody must have
 gone bankrupt in the middle or something like that. And mother said that according to the plans this house where we were was supposed to have been the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 reading room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  on the estates and so maybe there were some - adaptations to make it into a house at the last minute. Yes, it was a fitted bath. Another with these taps I'm telling you about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh once a week, Saturday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did the family have their meals, which room did you have your meals in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well what we called the kitchen - the living room, it was quite a good size.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Don't think we had - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So you had a sort of front room and a living kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Anything else at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well in the same room, the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of equipment did she have for cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh it was a - an old fashioned black stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When did you have breakfast, do you remember what time you would have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - I suppose about twenty past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What members of the family were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - if - if dad was at home - well I don't kn
ow, I expect - just mother and the two of us would. Or else he might have been in bed if he'd been on shift work. But it was - it wouldn't have been any novelty for us all to be together - for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did your father manage for his meals when he was on shift work, do you remember? You don't know what his shifts would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No, I can't tell you now, and of course when he was on the mail train that entailed him sleeping away part of the time too. I can't remember about him having to have speci
al meals at special times. I - as far as we were concerned - the mealtimes were fixed anyway you see, there was dinnertime when we came in from school and teatime when we came in from school. And it -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 And your father was usually there if possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I expect - oh yes, he would fit in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you normally have for breakfast, what would you usually eat and drink for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 breakfast time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well there was tea and - bread and dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have anything different on Sundays for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - in late - in - time we gravitated to having very small pieces of bacon. Might have - that might have been - Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Maybe not. I don't know, perhaps by the time - you see, I didn't leave school 'til I was s
eventeen. No, I - I think these little bits of bacon would be a special treat - that we would - arrive - perhaps by the time I was about - twelve or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But normally it was bread and dripping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. We used to fight to get the jelly part you know
, the - what we called the jelly, the - which is jelly, you know, the solidified brown part of it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You say you had your midday meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of things did you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - I suppose it varied 
a bit but - there - there was some small kind of - roast usually on Sunday, half a shoulder of mutton mother was awfully keen on, she didn't - believe in beef. And that was - cold - the next day, Monday. And - it was minced the next day. That would be Tue
s
day. And I - I used to have to go - for - three quarters of back collop and kidney, I don't know what back collop - is, but something called back collop and kidney. I - I think that had to serve for Wednesday and Thursday. That was - stewed generally or i
t
 could have been made into a pot pie. You know pot pies? Now that brings us to Friday. So I don't know what there was on Friday. But - Saturday we didn't have a proper dinner, we had what they used to call a - a tea dinner. Might have - might have - well,
 later on we used to have ham for this meal, you know, cooked - cooked ham. But - oh corned beef, there was - there was a corned beef period, I think that would be it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have puddings as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, there was always some sort of puddin
g. It was - on Sunday it was rice. Done in the oven and - oh I couldn't - I didn't like rice. And there's a story about when I was little, eat your rice Molly, you know and - it's hot. So in due course when I - couldn't say it was hot they'd say, eat your
 
rice Molly. It's a lot. Oh dear. I didn't like the rice. It was - there wasn't enough - there was too much rice for the amount of milk but oh it was solid. So that was Sunday. It was always rice, it was never anything else. And - Monday was washday so on 
S
unday night mother used to make a - some jelly and custard and that - that was part of the - the Monday meal. And I - the others may not have been quite so much - according to timetable. But we did get quite a lot of suet pudding. Which - yes, yes, that -
 
that was - solid. And we - an - an awful lot of potatoes, and - the rest of the family were - were - big - big eaters but it was potatoes and - an bread that they ate, I was always the skinny one you know. I didn't eat as much. But I was a - a slowcoach a
n
d I don't think they noticed. And then - we - got onto - barley pudding sometimes. Sometimes cooked in a pan sometimes cooked in the oven, but it wasn't - rolled barley like we have now, barley kernels you know, it was actual barley, and cooked with sugar
 and milk and - a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 raisins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 in it. I used to quite like that, we used to get one raisin at a time on each spoonful. Oh and ground rice we had sometimes. For pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of a tea did you have? Did you have anything to drink at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. Never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 at dinner.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you have for your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh just bread and jam. Might have got - there might have been a piece of - one piece of cake, if that, but - it was bread and jam that was the accepted thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 That was for the whole family, you all had the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. There was sometimes - some time when - boiled eggs came. That might have been Sunday. 'Cos - I can remember - Bobby and I having half an egg each, cut in two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You think that would probably be Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Most likely. But it - it was a real - treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have anything else when you went to bed, for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, if we wanted to we could have some bread and dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have anything to drink at suppertime?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think we were supposed to have anything to drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would your mother and father have a supper as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - I couldn't really say - I don't think they would have much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, mother used to bake our ow
n bread, for - for a good while, not right through. But by the time I was - thirteen, it was my daily duty to - to buy some bread at a certain shop, so she must have dropped that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she bottle any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she ever make any wine or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No. Just one time when me father brought a - one of these - bees wine things in. Do you know about these? Oh it - it's
 - it's something that's in quite a big jar and - the - the bees must be a kind of yeast, do you say yeast - really, but it was cloudy bit and it grows and grows and then they - they must be three weeks or something that you allow and then you pour off th
is liquid and add some fresh and start again. But I don't know - I don't suppose that lasted very long. But that was dad's experiment, not mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did either of them make any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't - I don't really think so, I - got 
on to a notion myself but - I don't know whether it originated with mother. For - lemon, glycerine and honey that was - I used to mix, she must have given me the money to buy the - things, I used to mix that but - I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What was that for, chest, coughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, coughs. She used to give us - hot lemon to go to bed with when we had colds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - beer? No. No, they - we were - teetotalers our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit, your father had an allotment didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he grow mostly vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Yes, he used to bring a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 sackful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  home on his back - I suppose on Saturday I think. And he grew a few flowers as well. Oh he used to sometim
es sell those. That - that was another little source of income, and vegetables too. From this allotment, yes. That was Sunday mornings when people used to come and - and want to buy things. So that - that would help out financially. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he grow fruit as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well just gooseberries, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did they ever buy any vegetables and fruit or didn't they need to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, yes, we used to have - buy them as well. Used - now what - used to go and buy - what they called twopennyworth o
f pot stuff, and the greengrocer used to give you a mixture of - carrot and turnip and leek, I suppose what was in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - later on in the period tinned peaches were a Sunday treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would that be before 1918? While you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, but that wasn't a regular - by then, it was if somebody was coming you know and not perhaps six - once in - three months or something like that, it was really very special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents keep any livestock for the family, any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh no. We always had a cat and a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many times a week did you eat meat, about five or six days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. About six days there must have been some sort of meat I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well this corned beef would be out of a tin. Otherwise - I don't think so. It - it wasn't so much - the thing then anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbits from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - she always did say she didn't like meat and she had a very small amount of meat so may - maybe that was part of it. But - she ate quite a lot of bread which was the staple diet of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father have more to eat than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 He had - the grown ups - you know, they would have a whole egg while we had a half egg, that's about all that I can think of
, they did get rather bigger portions but I mean they were bigger. We - we didn't - we just accepted it, we didn't resent them having - more, but I think they did have slightly more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, we could talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - we were pretty well forced to take what was there. If, by some chance, we just would not - or could not eat it - it was, the fact 
was that it would be there for our - next meal and it was. We jolly well had to do - get rid of that lot before we could have anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So if you left some food on the plate it came up at the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, you had to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I suppose it's good training in a way isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I don't know, perhaps - perhaps occasionally but I don't think regularly. Well of course it - it - it soon got that we - we - we did eat it at the first - serving. It didn't often happen that we - had it served up to us again because we'd left it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I don't think the question would arise much that - the salt where we could reach it, it was a small enough table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Oh yes. It was - it was generally expected that my brother who - who had a very big appetite, that he would ask for a second helping
 and - he would get it, mother quite - was quite pleased to - finish up whatever she had served and - start fresh the next time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. We - we weren
't supposed to - sit with it stuck up out of - well, like my brother used to do, of course he was younger. I can remember him being told to put them down. And I used to be in trouble for - not sitting up straight and - not just at mealtimes. I was going t
o be an old woman before I was a young one. I would sit humpy backed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - we weren't - supposed to but - my father quite often used to himself. Yes. Yes. And - later on - especially - when I had meals
 by myself I always read during - well now perhaps I watch T.V. and - if - that's available.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, we - no, we weren't supposed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When could you leave the table, did you have to wait until everyone had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, w
e were supposed to, we could say - please may I leave the table? And - maybe we would be allowed to go out to play before the others were ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal, when your father was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you ever remember your father having a packed meal or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, he used to - yes, mother - mother used to have to put up meals for him to take out. Yes, and when he was on the - on the mail.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of meal would he take?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - he was - he was very fond of - sandwiches made of - cheese and dates, I can remember that. Oh he - he was always very fond of - this is not so much his packed meal, he was fond of raw onion. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he ever take anything to drink when he was having a packed meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How was the meal served, did your mother use tureens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - I suppose my father was first. And then - I don't think it mattered very much then. I don't think it - I don't think there was any great thing made about that because - especially with it being in tureens, you were
n't just handed a plateful and that was it. It - it was - going round the different things so - I expect we would all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 served in the end about the same time, going round with the things. Daddy used to cut - well it was the - when it was the Sunday and there was something to carve, daddy normally was there and he used to carve the meat, that was his function.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves, you won't remember if your brother was only two years younger will you, did he have a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, he had a high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who would feed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well mother would feed him I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was his high chair at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, she wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - it seemed to me that everything I - everything I said was wrong you see, she - she would always, contradict me, or if I came home and I said, well the teacher said, what the teacher said was wrong. So I got into the way of 
- I didn't say anything, I didn't talk to her much because - I didn't get any - response.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she show affection at all in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I suppose she did but I - I think she was rather a cold woman really. My sister - since then has used my very sam
e expression, she said mother was a cold woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No, she wouldn't - wasn't a person I would turn to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well he wasn't the
re so much but - he did make much more effort. Specially, this - this was - well it would be - before I was thirteen, no doubt it's getting later in the period, but - when I was going to bed - then he would stop me and - and - and start to talk to me then
 and - he - he did really - he did try, he wanted to - to bring me out and possibly - possibly he - he saw that I wasn't as communicative as I should be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would he actually show affection in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - that depends what you mean, I mean, we u
sed to kiss him goodnight and - and mother as well if it comes to that, but it was a matter of form I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 If you had any worries could you share them with your father or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I - I could have done, not that I had so much - such worries
 I mean really I mean, really would we, we wouldn't. We wouldn't have thought of them as being worries and - and things that they would - be likely to help in settling, we would - we were happy enough you know. But I - if I had had some - something explos
ive - I think I'd have been more likely to have - tried to get hold of daddy than mother with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 They expected obedience. I don't know what else to say. I got - that once or twice I was sup
posed to be cheeky, you know, I used to get - smacked and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brother in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well like - I've already said, I was supposed to look after him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No. No, and that's a - that's a - that's a thing I've - debated with myself in later life but - it never seemed to occur. When I was a child myself, it - it - they didn't - they didn't enter into it if there were - any 
rows among the other kids. And - and - I don't know whether you're going to - come on this, but - you see, among - we were - rather small community being in this unfinished estate and - such children as were there generally - got on pretty well together, 
we - there wasn't anybody else and we - were - sometimes rather assorted ages and - boys and girls all mixed together - with or without - ganging up separately. And - I don't think we had - that kind of row where we did hit each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What kind of people do you think your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 parents hoped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Mother actually - prophesied I would go into domestic service the same as she went, she didn't seem to think there was any other possible kind of future. And - I think daddy was more - more ambitious really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh I don't know, except - getting work and getting some money. 'Cos - there was this - this - it gradually dawned on us there was a background of - of
 not being well enough of you know and that we would need to - to work hard and - and get a job, 'cos everybody didn't have a job. And - it was up to us. But I think that only came - gradually and - and later in the period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Anything else at all that they taught you was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - they - before daddy went to the war they were - both - practicing Christians, but they - they got out of that and - and - we were brought up - as chapelgoers and were supposed to - observe }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  laws and - if that's the kind of thing you mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh they - they didn't - it never came into it, they didn't swear themselves and - and we - we didn't, we would never have dreamt of it but - it would have been - thoroughly disapproved of if it had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen, you said you were smacked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I got - yes, I got some real good thrashings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who did the smacking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How often would you be smacked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - it - it - it wasn't a regular feature, I suppose once a fortnight or so on the average. I - I can - the first thing that I can - really remember - was - for some reason
 I'd said, naughty mother, and I was about two. This was before I came back to Gateshead, I can remember - it was - just beside the door between - there was a scullery there and - and the living room. So she gave - she gave me a good smacking and then she
 
said, say that again. And by then I was thoroughly cowed so I said it again. And I got another lot. And I certainly can remember that. And what I resented partly was that - if Bob did anything wrong - I was always lugged into it, it was those kids you kno
w
, I was always blamed. And - if - if - if I did anything wrong of course he - he was - he had nothing to do with that. Oh I - I'm - I'm discovering all sorts of jealousies now that I didn't - properly realize. Oh yes, she - and even later on she was very 
handy with - smacking me fact when we got a bit too big for a smacking with a belt. There was a belt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 A proper thrashing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. And - I had a grandma that - that lived at Ongham at the time, she'd moved from Sunderland. Ongeham they called it, a v
illage. And - she had - a stick, they called a mon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
ey stick that hung behind the door. They had a monkey, they had had a monkey like, I've got a picture of myself looking at the monkey. But I - I think by then they hadn't the monkey, but they still had the
 monkey stick. She used to threaten us with this monkey stick. It was quite a - quite the thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father ever have to smack you or thrash you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't remember him ever doing it, he was - he used to give us some tellings off sometimes wh
en we got older for - wanting to stay out late, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember any other particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well she - she didn't thrash us for this - this one. It's a bit comic - too. One Sunday my father was going
 to bring somebody home for dinner. It was something to do with this U.P.W. you see, well this was going to be very special indeed. So - I was - supposed to be helping with the dinner. And - the - there was this jar of dripping, and I upset this lot, and 
p
oor soul, what a carry on when she was trying to get this special dinner ready and there - amount of dripping all over the show. So she did - she didn't hit me then. She said, either go out for a walk and not come back til three o'clock. Eeh. Oh it must h
ave been awful mustn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - I used to have a kind of - toughness, you know, I used to try not to cry until - you know, until I couldn't stop myself, my brother used to cry straight away an
d - get himself off, but - most times I used to resent it because I - I didn't think I deserved it honestly. I used to try to behave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more i
mportant part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh they - they worked as a team, they'd stick together won't they, they, they both - a parent - whatever - morals we were taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I think most times mother tried to have a little cake, a little spice loaf.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you receive presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - yes, there was generally something. It wasn't anything big. I don't know. Might - might get a small - box of chocolates or - a quarter pound box of chocolate. Christmas I generally used to get a - a doll. I didn't like dolls much either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have any guests in, any friends in for tea on your birthday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so, might have happened the odd time but it - it wasn't an 
expected thing. Other children - I used to know other children who did have parties and - they didn't generally ask me. Because - of course we didn't ask them. But then I used to hear about these parties and wonder why we couldn't have parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Perhaps you couldn't afford them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 That must have been it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Do you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day, you say you used to get a doll for Christmas and you didn't like dolls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I - well I don't know,
 well partly think that - they always got broken before I could do much about them, anyway my brother used to break them. And - I always used to long for a teddy bear but I never got one. There was a Christmas stocking in the morning and - there was - I c
a
n remember the small of orange more than anything on Christmas morning. And - packet of biscuits generally. That was one little - this - not Christmas, but one little treat we used to get occasionally was when my father came in on a Sunday morning it must
 
have been at the end of a spell in Birmingham, this was rather special and it would only be once a month maybe. He came in early on the Sunday morning and there was a little packet of biscuits for - one for my brother and one for me, one of these with abo
u
t six biscuits in it and there was a packet of - chocolate biscuits for mother. That really was something special that other people didn't get. But - we're back to Christmas now, we - we did hang stockings up over this oven door, I don't know quite why it
 
had to be over the oven door. And then we came downstairs in the morning, it wasn't over the bottom of the bed like they do - and - usually there was - a friend of mother's who had been in service with her was - invited - for teatime at Christmas, I don't
 think she was there dinnertime. But - we did - we used to have a duck generally, and - it might have been later still after - beyond your period we had a goose. But there was a special effort made for Christmas and there was a little Christmas pudding.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you go to chapel at all on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Don't think so - I - I don't think they had services on Christmas Day at the - at the non-conformist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have any musical instruments in the home, did anybody play any musical instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh now - later on - the - a piano came into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 this sitt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 ing room. How - how old am I? Is it just - yes, this is - yes, this is still in this house, yes, the piano was in that house and it wasn't in the next house. That's right. And - I was supposed to be g
oing to learn the piano, and - I was sent for three quarters, you know, you used to pay by the quarter. I was getting on all right. And then when - it was nearly time for the next one, well I think it was actually time, instead of giving me the money to p
a
y for the next quarter - mother told me to tell the - the teacher that I wouldn't be coming any more, this was the first I'd heard of it. And it wasn't until years afterwards it dawned on me why, it was because she must have found out my young sister was 
g
oing to be born you see, and I hadn't a clue. I'd just started the secondary school then and I did have homework to do and - you know, it - it was allowed to be thought that - I was having too much to do, what with practicing music and - homework as well.
 But that must have been it really, that there was going to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did anyone else play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Used to play card games inside. Whist - they were great whist friends. Used to go to whist drives and they used to win - some prizes. They were - pretty good. Well that was what they did on Christmas Day as well, used to play cards at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Any other games apart from card games did your parents play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes. Yes. I did a lot of reading myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Newspapers, magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, there were -
 I suppose there was a daily paper, and - something like - Answers my father used to get, a paper called - a weekly paper called Answers, it was short for Answers to Correspondents I think originally. And he got - Tit-Bits for a while, perhaps he didn't g
et them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So you remember your mother and father reading then do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 My father used to read an awful lot. I expect mother didn't have that much time to read. And - we as kids, we used to read a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember a funeral in the family in that period before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations when you were a schoolgirl? Did you ever go visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - not - not very much. There was this same friend who used to come on Christmas Day, I can remember being at her house and - reading What Katie Did At School and - which was in her bookcase, but - I had this - I had these grandparents at Onge
ham and during the school holiday I was allowed to stay there for - perhaps a fortnight, I don't really now how long.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were they your mother's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, they were my father's parents. And - I suppose we - we did go the odd time to see my moth
er's - mother and - it was a - a step father as she had by then. They still lived at Sunderland. And the odd time they used to - came to see us too. So he was - the second husband of - mother's mother was an examiner, I don't - I think he was retired - as
 
soon as I knew him, and - he used to breed - little - little tiny dogs. Yes. Oh I'm going to lose the name of them now, I know it quite well. That wasn't the name. Anyway, it was from there usually that we had this - we had a perpetual dog you see, when w
e always had a dog - and - mother and dad used to think he was rather a character this - this old gentleman. Now I had a great grandfather that I can remember. It's not so unusual today when people marry so young but it - it - it was quite a rarity then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 By then he - he was living in - in a - a room - at these grandparents at Ongeham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When you were taken visiting friends or relations who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh the whole family went as a - as a body.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever visit neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You mean sort of next door? There was very little of that, mother discouraged - us going into other peoples houses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 And - during the war, when my father was away and - well off course most of the men would be away, she and - another war - widow, y
ou - from the opposite corner, they got very friendly and there - there was a good bit of to and froing then, and for one short time I actually had to go and sleep with her, she must have had nerves or something. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But a - apart from that - there wasn't much coming in and out of houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you taken out shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well I used to have to go a lot of the messages, I had to go for the - the food shopping. And - otherwise - I was just taken shopping when it was my turn to have something bought or to - to look for something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You said you remembered a little bit about birthday and Christmas presents, could you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. Well - one thing is that - over the years we - my - daddy did build up a set of Dickens for me, giving me one book at a time for birthdays and I suppose also for Christmas. I never got Martin }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Chuzzlewit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  so far. And - also I would occasionally have a new coat or something liked that which ranked as a birthday present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Yes. Well, I can only remember - one - yes, oh - oh well anyway, I - I must have been five, because - a new baby had just bee
n born who is - the person is five years younger than me, and mother was going to see the - the mother and baby and - daddy was going to look after Bobby and me. I had the impression that he was going to take us to the pictures but I'm not quite sure whet
her I can be right as that would just be 1910, however there was this great elation because daddy was going to take us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember anywhere else you went with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - I told you about going to the garden, I think most of
 the time there was - there was only - dad there. I can't - I can't really remember going out with him apart from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember any other outings with your parents such as on Bank Holidays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 We - I don't think we were people for having days out - we were exceptional in going away for holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever go away for a holiday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. I should think maybe alternate years we - we went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 For how long would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I - I don't know whethe
r it'd be a week or a fortnight. One - I can't - I can only remember very small things about the first one when we stayed at a farm house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember when that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, but I've lost the name now, it's - in - Teesdale. Oh dear, that's s
illy of me, I know it so well. Yes, I probably will when I'm thinking about something else. It wasn't as far as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you come to go there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't really know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you know which members of the family went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 The four of us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember what you did whilst you were on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh we mostly went for walks, that was always our speciality. And I can remember - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 mother squealing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  when some frogs jumped in the wood, and - there was one place we often went to, it was
 a sort of - reddish - high bank beside the path and it had - four or five long narrow - curved holes in it, they - it - called the Fairy Cupboards I could never make out what this was, I would like to go back and find this and see what it was. Yes. And -
 the - there was a big boy and - my father gave him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 some roller skates, that must have been I think partly his }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 recompense}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  for the hospitality of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  farmhouse. It was on the village green, it overlooked the village green. Long time afterwards I - I went ba
ck and I saw the house and - recognised that would be it by it's position. Of course it was much smaller than my recollection. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you go anywhere else for a holiday that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. We got into the way of taking a - a country co
ttage and - we had to take everything and tinned food did come into there to some extent. Sheets and towels and all that sort of thing. One - later on, one of the later ones was Keswick. We went to Allenheads and Hayden Bridge. Places like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 All the four of you was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. We were actually on holiday at - Felton - when - war broke out and daddy was recalled, he had to go back, but we didn't go back straight away. Oh, I'm not quite telling you the truth, quite often this - Maggie Davies and t
he friend of mother's who had been in service with her, quite often she was with us on the holiday. I suppose it depended how many beds there were. Oh we used to like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You did a lot of walking on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - oh yes, we walked tremendously
. I used to get the job of - going myself to buy eggs at the - farms and - in the middle of this - I used to like it. I took an interest in flowers and - birds and so on. There was one time daddy used to go trout fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Th
at would most likely be at Felton before he was recalled. It - it wasn't a very long - episode anyway, but I can remember we did get some little trout to eat. We were excited.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days, when you were a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - in the mornings there was this - housework, I - you know, I always - did do - I told you about the washing the floors and cleaning the taps, well - it - the whole morning was spent on that. I think sometimes I was ready in time to go
 out and buy the - the corned beef or whatever it was for this - Saturday tea dinner. But for a - a period - we used to - we did go to the pictures, this was - this is - right, there was a - a hall called the Shipcote Hall, not very far - Shipcote - which
 - cote - it's supposed to originate from sheepcote. The whole area is called - if - it was Shipcote school I went to as well. And - it was a penny each for children to go in on a Saturday afternoons. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Oh - there were - must have been - I think there must ha
ve been - thousands, you know, more than a thousand anyway in this hall when we were first - there were great big long benches you know, and when we first went in - we were lucky if we could get somebody to let us have three inches to perch on at the end,
 
and - a man would come with a long, long rod and be would be shouting, close up to the middle, and you would actually poke some of the people from the distance with this stick and induce them to move towards the middle and - by the time he got us organise
d we were a long way from the end of these seats you know and squads more were sitting in there, so I used to have to take my brother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
And - and later days I don't know whether he revolted at having to be looked after by me, but - later on - a lady at the t
op of the street used to want me to take her little girl and she paid for both of us which was quite an inducement. They were mostly serials that were on. Was always what we called a comic. This was silent films and somebody used to play the piano while i
t was on you know, and - oh there were the - Exploits of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Elaine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
, and the Perils of Pauline and things like this and - yes, the heroine would be - on the - bound to the railway line with the engine rapidly approaching and suddenly it came to an end and we had to go back next week to see what next would happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So you enjoyed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh we did, it was great thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How about Sundays in those days, what did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - well - I think - for a period we went to chapel in the mornings 
with dad. At - we certainly went to Sunday school in the afternoon. The - chapel where we went to was quite a long way from where we lived. Until after the war and then of course - I don't know what went wrong but for some reason we went to a smaller - on
e which was nearer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of chapel was it, which denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
United Methodist. And - at first we were in what they called the primary - Sunday school. It was big, you know, I'm surprised now when thinking back how - what a big population t
here was and - the really little ones used to sit along the front in - a long row, there must have been I think about thirty of them, all in one long row on little squat - chairs with - round - round wooden back. And - the rest of us were - more or less g
r
ouped behind on - on rather higher chairs. And that some - place in the proceedings, the - the small ones had to go out of a door and - down about three steps into a different room to have their story separately, and I can remember now them - standing up 
and they - they never carried their chair in front you know, they still carried their chair round their bottom and walked along like that. There was this peculiar little procession - slowly - ambling out. Then there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 a bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  more space for us and we got in
to little circular groups each with a teacher and had - Bible stories. They must have been quite progressive because - we used to have - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 crayons}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  and paper and - do pictures of the story afterwards and then there were some little - oh - strips, coloured str
ips that we had to weave into mats, that was for the man that was let down on his bed to Jesus and I think it served for some other story as well. I don't know what else but - you know, we thought this was great and - and - looking back now I think they -
 they were with it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you have different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, in the main. In the main we did. When I was - when I was quite little it was the thing to have a white frock on Sunday. And - some of the little girls used to wear their whi
te frock on Monday at school to dirty it out but - you know, we were above that, my mother washed on Monday and the frock went straight into the wash. That was the attitude. And later on we went into the - what we called the big Sunday school you know, th
e
 - I don't know how old we would be - and - oh we read from the Bible then and the bits between the hymns. It was pretty - pretty dim - and dull you know. And later on they wanted me to be a teacher in this primary - school. And I don't think that lasted 
very long, but anyway that would be beyond the period I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you play games on Sunday, did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well now, yes, this - this is a bit mixed because - my father had had a very strict upbringing
 and there hadn't to be any - any work or - or any - any buying from the shops or anything like that on Sundays, but - it - this quite often slipped you know and - there - there were things being done that were not - strictly orthodox. When I went to my g
r
andma's at Ongeham, his parents, she - she was very - still very strict indeed about Sundays. And - I - if I was just happily singing to myself that was stopped, I must only sing hymns. She was terrible. And - I - remember one time I - stood behind the do
or and sort of jumped out and said boo to my - this cousin that's five years younger, and I was in sore trouble about that, not - not for doing it but for doing it on Sunday, I mustn't play games on Sunday. It was - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Your parents weren't quite as strict?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, they were growing out of it. And - well, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 later}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  on dad used to send for - a batch of secondhand papers, Sexton Blakes and things like that, he used to change one lot and you paid a bit extra and got another lot, and this was a Sunday transaction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did both your parents go to church or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, at - at night they both went. Mother was busy with the dinner - I'd peel potatoes and things like that before I - went, but she - naturally was busy with - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How often would you say your parents went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well, dad went - every week, twice a - twice on Sunday, mother would go once on Sunday. But - you know, he went to the war - when I was nine and - this - character - characteristic was changed. I - I think the war 
was responsible and - there wasn't a strictness about going to chapel afterwards. We were still supposed to go but - they didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother still go with you while you father was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I can't remember about that, no, I think it must have - yes, tailed off then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You didn't go at night with them, you just went in the morning and to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I can't - I don't think we went at night. There were the chapel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 
anniversaries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  which was the highlight you know, it was in June. Don't
 you know about chapel anniversaries. Oh well, all the kids from - both the Sunday schools were expected to say a piece. A piece of poetry. And they rigged up some sort of - wooden platform, oh a big affair - round the pulpit and so on you know and down t
o
 floor level and - all the kids were on this and here again the - little girls were supposed to have white - dresses, but I can remember a green velvet one I had one time and it must have been new. Mother was doing a funny motion to me from the congregati
o
n you know, I couldn't understand what was the matter with her, but this thing - it was a pinafore dress and one shoulder had slipped off, you see, and I was supposed to pull this up and look elegant, but - I - I - must have been a bit dim, I didn't know 
what was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - I should think about six, I can't - I don't know whether I still have a photograph of myself with this green velvet, I had it a long time and I did like that one. Yes. Oh yes. Yes. And - well - I told you ab
out my baby sister didn't I, this still comes in the time. Well - by then I was in my first year at the secondary school and I - I'd - one of the pieces of poetry I'd learnt was the Arsenal at Springfield. And this was just after the war you know, when wa
r and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 armaments}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 and so on were very much in people minds, so - the teacher at Sunday school wanted to know who was going to say what, and I suggested this and - she accepted without hearing it or anything you know, I expect she thought, well that's one less
 I don't have to teach. And I must have thought, that's one less I don't have to learn, you know, and that was O.K. So - this was the day that Lesley, my sister, was going to be christened. And when they called my name the parents of the baby hadn't arriv
e
d and I was so disappointed because they weren't going to hear me. Anyway, I said this piece and - you - nobody ever clapped in chapel at all you know, but I could feel that there was an impression, you know, almost a sensation. And just as I sat down the
 - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 vestry }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
r at the back opened and in came the little procession of - mother and daddy and the baby. But they told me afterwards they had heard me through the door, so that - that - settled that to some extent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any Sunday school outings, do you ever remember going on Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, there used to be a Sunday school treat once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did you go for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - we went - most often to some field, there was one at - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Wishingwell
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  Woods, which is - not f
ar south of Gateshead, it's in walking distance. And - I think we would likely go on the tramcar. And there was - one I can remember, it was at Plawsworth, but if - why I remember it that the - the man in charge called it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 Plawsworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  and mother - mother - m
other was amused about this. I have to say that my parents, although they - they spoke - Tyneside, they weren't as broad as some of the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in, do you remember anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. There was one - most unusual thing. We were going to go to the gymnasium at - at the chapel. So this thing got organised and low and behold my father was the instructor, and I'd never had any idea that he had any special claims to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2371844\charrsid15804465 athleticism}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  so 
anyway there were three classes, well - the children, I think I must have been about seven now because as I say I was just turned nine when the war broke out and smashed everything up, and - I think we had sand shoes but otherwise there was no stipulation
 
about costume, it was boys and girls together. And we did - very much the same sort of thing that we did in drill at school but also - we did - what daddy called Swedish drill, that I used to like, it was just consisted of - marching - sometimes in one si
n
gle row but going into all sorts of patterns, in and out of a rosette and getting out again. And sometimes - sort of counter marching that you - went into ranks of two or four and eight and then - I used to like that. And we had - I don't think we called 
t
hem Indian clubs, but - the big - the big hefty ones shaped like bottles are Indian clubs, but anyway we had some smaller clubs that - were - lighter and curved at the bottom, the children had these. After - after the children had gone home we were still 
t
here you see because this - this was daddy and I think that I - I - my impression is it was all done on the same evening. Then - there was the - the ladies. Oh well, they would be girls about twenty mostly, but mother went and - another person who was a l
i
ttle bit older mind, weren't really so old but to us they seemed old. So they both wore - a navy - rather full skirt - down to about their knees which was very daring really you know. And - a white blouse. But the - the others had - a gym tunic and of cou
r
se everybody had long black stockings anyway, that was no problem. And - our daddy had - I think you call it a single, a - sort of - vest thing with - with red - up the neck and at the - they were very short sleeves, at the sleeves and - white flannel tro
users, I don't now where he got those from.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where had he done these things before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I still don't know. Honestly it was - I was very proud and all that but I - I - I - I didn't know that he had this background. There was another fellow called - Norman Self who got dressed like that and - helped him afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 This was organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, and you know, the - they had progressive - now they had - parallel bars and - a horse, they call it a buck now, you know, these - leather - 
efforts and mattresses, so - they must have spent an immense amount on this, they might have got the whole lot secondhand from somewhere but even so - it was a big undertaking. And it was seemed to me to be flourishing. Don't - I never heard anything abou
t daddy getting any money on the reason for this but that could be a possibility - to help the coffers, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Any other social activities organised by the chapel can you remember taking part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - well they used to have a bazaar once a
 year. What - they didn't - they called it a sale of work then and it was more a sale of work than most of such efforts are nowadays. And - and people were supposed to - order something in advance if they could, like - a nightdress and somebody else would
 
buy the material and spend a long time handmaking a nightdress. And - there was a bran tub. And we would have - a penny or something, that was our - lot. And - the bran tub - was a disillusionment oh - but they were - they were - it was all tripe anyway, 
it was - no good. There was always a marvelous tea. And then - there used to be - what they called an effort during the year, the young men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 s effort and the young women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
s effort and I don't know who elses' effort but - just to be a concert generally. It - it - yes, it - it was lively.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. I was - they didn't have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  choir, but when - later on when - I think I must have been about - fourteen or so when we went to this other chapel, then I was in the choir, not
 that I could sing but it was the thing to do. The girls were in the choir and the boys were in the football club. And they used to have nice socials there, social evenings with some - bit of dancing in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the chapel run any temperance club and were you remember of that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - before we leave this chapel I - I've remembered now about the magic lantern. They didn't - I don't think they called it a Band of Hope, I don't know whether it had a title but this was on Monday nights, every week 
and - we had star cards of - at - you know, for attendance, they stamped our card with a - a star, I - I don't know whether we got something for good attendance. And they marked it in the register. And - I'm - what I can remember it was mostly hymns. And 
-
 the hymns were put on the slide and there were the most - soppy looking angles on the - on the slides, oh they - they did - they did look formless, you know, without any character at all, and we sang while the words were - on the screen. And then there w
o
uld be - Bible stories that were illustrated with these - slides. Oh we quite liked it. And then daddy had something to do with this as well. I think he sometimes operated the projector. I think he must have been the spare parts man that filled in at diff
e
rent - yes, and that was - that was quite - now we're on about the temperance. I - I don't think the - I don't think the chapel had anything directly connected with - with that but I did, when I was about eleven - that's just about the edge of your period
 - well - that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 takes me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 up to thirteen, I joined the Cadets at temperance, a separate organisation, the - the grown ups were the Sons of Temperance, kids were the Cadets of Temperance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 This wasn't to do with the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, it was a - separate hall called the Westfield Hall. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you do there'd?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - oh - oh yes, every time we put our hand up and said, I solemnly promise - and - a whole lot you know, and - the - the - we had - hymns with temperance words, but they were mostl
y - hymn tunes that we knew already. Was, my drink is water, bright water, bright water, my drink is water right from a crystal stream and things like that. And there was generally somebody who would come and - give - tell us a story. And they had - they 
h
ad - people from the children themselves as - officials. As the - the chairman and the secretary at least, I - I don't know whether there'd be anymore. 'Cos I was very soon the secretary. And I used to - write what happened you know, take minutes, I didn'
t know it was called taking minutes, and then read them out the next week at - I'm a bit surprised myself now because it makes me ages to do me minutes these days, I do it, but I did them on the job then and they got away fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think of anything else concerned with the chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, for - for a long time. And - this comes back to - something we said before about - who was served 
first at mealtimes. It's rather - as it worked out nobody was allowed to start until grace had been said and we all started together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who said grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well daddy did for a long time and then he would ask one of us to. I don't remember mother ever saying grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who taught you to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I should think it would be mother. It goes back too far to remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father take an interest in politics and do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - I don't - think right at the beginning he took much active interest but - we did know that we were supposed to be Liberals. But - this would probably happen during the war too that - he became a Socialist and we were avowed Labour people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why do you think he held those views, why do you think he was a Liberal in the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I expect it was just that his family had been Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why do you think he changed during the war, any particular reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well I just have to speculate and - well you see - I'm so strongly - Socialist myself it seems to be obvious that people with any sense - are of the same persuasion. No, I wouldn't 
know of any great turning point but I do think that the his experience in the war, seeing - so - so much - waste of life and - property - for - you know, for no valid result that we could see, I - I think that - made him - want to stick up for the ordinar
y people more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you know what your mother's views were? Did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
She didn't take any active interest but it was just - she - accepted - what dad - I think, without any special - argument. Well she - mother - mother 
- I have to say looking back as I've been up - in connection with this like, I think she was a - an - outstanding - individualist, but - as far as the politics go they - they seemed to see eye to eye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh I can't - the end of the war? 19 - 1920 - 1918 - well I - I can't exactly remember her - going and putting her vote but - I - I - I know that - we were - expected them - to vote and the - the kids used to make a lot 
of to - do about voting in the streets at that time. We had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I can't remember him actually going to vote but I know it - it was understood that he always - had registered h
is vote, and if mother was entitled to vote she would - I'm quite sure she would as well. And I was going to tell you about the basters that the kids had. These were - some sort of ball, perhaps made of screwed up paper, perhaps with a stone in the middle
 of, on - on a long string and they were supposed to - hit each other with this if they weren't of the proper political }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 persuasion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 . Yes, they ganged themselves up with this. And - they used to sing as well, vote, vote, vote for whoever it was. For he's sure
 to win the war, I don't know why it had to be the war. You can buy a penny gun and we'll make the other one run. It - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Up to when would your father vote for the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I suppose - up 'til about 1913. But he - there wouldn't be any elections during the war would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Women had the vote somewhere about 1918 or 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 1918. 1919, yes. I think - you had to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 twenty-eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  before you could vote, or something - but it's no good arguing about that now. Yes, yes. I - I - really t
hink women got - women got the vote just after the war, now I remembering, there'd been all the carry on with suffragettes before the war, and they got nowhere, but then women had come out and worked so well in the factories and so on that they were given
 the vote. So 1918. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure, to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I shouldn't think so, but in - in the Civil Service there - there seemed to be one disability that - I understand they weren't allowed - for a long time to stand as a candidate in council election or anything. Later on my father did stand in 
a - council election, in a hopeless ward purposely. And so whether they'd altered the ruling or whether it - it was only that he - he couldn't stand if he was elected so it was all right to stand where it was hopeless.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was your father an actual member of a political party before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I - I doubt it. I don't think he was a member of the Liberal party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well, no - not - not until later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I shouldn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - they - they went out a lot. And later on I - I d
o know he used to go to whist drives and they also did some dancing. But - I'm - not very sure whether they'd been going to whist drives all the time or whether they went for walks, you see I don't think there was enough - money to - to spend on going out
 practically every night. I think they must have gone for walks. But they were often out. Of course daddy used to read an awful lot, in - when he was in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well, she didn't belong to
 any clubs or anything of that sort. No, I - I think - it would be go - I think she used to get fed up and go for a walk or - I just can't - I just knew mother was going out, you accepted that, but I can't think now where she would go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself and with whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well she - you know, there was this shift work and then there was daddy being away at the war so she would be without - adult companionship in the evenings quite a lot. So - I think that - I - I'm speculating, 
I think she just must have gone out for walks to get away from the house, after she did gradually get into whist drives and during the war she did team up with a Mrs Thompson who's husband was also at the war who - lived almost opposite, I told you I slep
t with her - for a little time, so - they used to go out together. And Mrs Thompson used to come and sit in our house sometimes. She used to lend me books, I liked that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When did your father get home from work in the evenings, you said he was on shifts so that's not really applicable is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, it - it varied. Especially when he was on the train you see, he was away for more than twenty-four hours at a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many evenings on an average would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 At home, in the house? I don't know. I really can't think of them sitting round and - in the house in the evenings at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother go to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, they were strictly T.T.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I - I've no knowledge of anything apart from this - P.T. and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, no, this was all very wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, any boot clubs, sick clubs, funeral clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 They just had a normal insurance did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh they - they - there were several penny a week insurances - on our lives, that's one of them I'm still paying. 
Oh yes. They always reckoned to save up for anything beforehand, you know, they - they didn't - believe in hire purchase which was just coming into - vogue then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 get on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  with your brothers and sisters, it would have been your brother chiefly, the little ones when you were thirteen did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - yes. No, no, no, Lesley's in the period. Lesley was born in 1918. Just - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did your get on with your brother and your sister then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I got on all right with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you feel about your mother having a baby with that sort of gap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well, you know - they - they didn't - they didn't mention it to me - by - I could tell - after a while, especially when other people were asking me how my mother was and so on,
 everybody else thought I was in their confidence, they never mentioned it to me. It was just one of those things - I had to put up with it and - the day came and - I was told that I wasn't going to school for a fortnight, I was going to have to stay and 
l
ook after the house while mother was in bed with this baby. Well - everybody seemed to be pleased enough about the baby, I think it was - the neighbours welcomed this you know, they thought it was a - a bit of a - I don't want to say a joke exactly, but t
hey were pleased - pleased about this - happening after such a long time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 
And - mother - mother seemed quite pleased about it and so did daddy and - well she was a nice - nice baby and - of course I got - a lot of - the - job of looking after her but - I li
ked her and - oh but she did used to cry at - I don't know how long, it must have been months, every night she used to cry from six o'clock 'til eight o'clock. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I was supposed to be doing homework by then you know and I - I used to have - to walk about with her for these two hours. I don't know why it was, mother must have got a bad back or something at the time, she wasn't able to lift her much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 There was only Bobby that you could have felt close to in this period, did you feel close to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think so. No, I rather resented him - being a boy and - and not - being expected to do any of the jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 As a child who did you play with, Bobby or neighbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - oh we - both. There was a whole crowd of us used to play together - in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You played mostly in the street did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. I - I did mention that this was just a party finished estate and there was a lot of space. But - outside our - house the - there - the - there was no pavement, there was just th
e kerbstone, and then the - the road wasn't properly made, it had - rather rounded big sandstone - stones with - I suppose soil in between and that seemed to be the main - venue for - the games. And - I - now I wonder how it was nobody found fault with th
e noise that we made because we must have been noisy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there gardens on this estate, did you ever play in the gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 One - one lot of house - well - yes, one lot of houses had gardens, no we didn't go and - play there, their gardens was - 
strictly for produce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever play in other homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Very little, mother - mother didn't - approve of me going into anybody's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But as long as you'd got plenty of room you'd be all right outside wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember what games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Squads and squads of games. I think the - the most usual one was what we called tredgie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How do you spell that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I - I've never seen it spelled. But put tredgye all right and it sounds Scandinavian and - and later on it turned out to be - very }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 - what they call Danish rounders. I - I think we must be - a survival of language there. But - the only thing is we didn't have a bat, we just had to throw the ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you play it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well
 - the two bigger - biggest people - split the rest up into two sides, one side was in and the other side was out. And - they started with - the little ones to throw the ball first, and you could - you must not throw it backwards but you could throw it at
 
any angle otherwise and if one of the others who were fielding caught this you were out. While - as soon as you'd thrown the ball you had to run to the first bay on the - the right diagonally and - also if - one person one person was running and - one of 
t
he others was able to throw the ball and hit the bay before the person arrived at it then the - the approaching person was out. And when the next person was throwing a ball of course you ran to your next bay and so on. And - gradually people were whittled
 down, they were out until there was only one man left, he was called tredgye man, and he was allowed to throw backwards if he liked. And he had to go right round the whole four bays and come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Like rounders but instead of hitting with a stick you threw the ball?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. And if he got back then everybody was in again, but if he didn't the other side was in. It was very like rounders. And - we had a game called Hot Rice which did need a bat. Do you know Hot Rice? So one person had the bag and the
re was a ball and - everybody else - used to have to try to hit any part of that persons body with the ball, if that happened the - the bat holder had to drop it immediately and the person who had done the deed picked up the bat and goes on. Oh yes, and a
gain there you defended yourself with this bat and if somebody else caught it - that was another way of - of getting the bat and - you could all run about, it could be a really hot game. By the way there again we used to say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 keep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  for catch. And that's Latin, you know, we had quite a different vocabulary for our games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Is that particularly to the area - to Gateshaed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 T
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 yneside I should think. And there was cold rice, a variation of this where the person stood still and - it was only the legs
 then that had to be hit with the ball. Ah - and they didn't - even - mustn't turn round you know, they had to screw round. Oh you know that. I - I wrote a list of this. Yes, then there was. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 
Up from Monday and - for this we went round a corner the gable en
d of the house next door to us and - there was a ball and somebody threw it up and shouted, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday - I suppose Sunday and each of you had been given a name previously and if you - I don't know - don't rememb
er it properly but you were supposed to catch it if it was yours, 'cos you would be - you were out if you didn't catch it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
We used to play shops, the girls anyway used to play shops. And - for this we had to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 goodies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
