If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage and do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born? Was your mother ever ill any other time, apart from when she had the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't remember her being ill in bed. She used sometimes not to - to be well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 She had the baby at home did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember any other incidents about when the baby was born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - I - I don't quite know what sort of thing you mean. There was just a - she - she would shout downstairs, what are you doing Molly? And I would say, I'm washing the dishes. And about ten minutes afterwards, what are you doing? I'
m washing the - see it got to be a joke with them afterwards, that there was such a lot of dishes, but I - I cheated a little bit, I used to have a book to - at the same time when there was nobody - to see what I was up to, but there were pretty intermina
ble dishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother have a midwife or a doctor or what, do you remember anything about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - I think there - there was - I don't really - no, I wasn't in on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby, you said not really, where did this aunt come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
She didn't have - she didn't have a permanent home. She had always been in service, this was my mother's younger sister. In domestic service until the war and then she went into - munitions and moved about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 country}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 a bit, I know who went to Selby. But - by now I expect she was back on Tyneside and in service again I think she would be in Newcastle but - she didn't have a home of her own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So you said your parents didn't really have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 There weren't any in the town itself. And we had very few relatives really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You went to this grandma's didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How much did you see of your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well - I'd - probably see them about once in three months 
or so, these people, because they used to come and see us occasionally too. But - mother's mother - I - I didn't see so often. Perhaps - once in six months. There was one time - oh she came to stay with us. I'd been - I'd been to see them, they lived in }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 Sunderland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
, she had a - a second husband and I told you that they - he used to breed these tiny - tiny little - dogs you know, so - this time grandma Gillie was - so this time my grandma Gillie was going to come to stay with us and - she didn't come when - q
uite - when she was expected, so I was sent down to where the trams stopped, which was - you know - quite a little way out of the town, to look for her. So I looked and I didn't see anybody. And then - oh I think while I was there I had to get some - the 
b
read from the bread shop and when I went along there - I - I saw one, a little dog just like these, so I came home and said I couldn't see grandma Gillie but I'd seen somebody with a little dog just like. So mother said, well go back, that'll be her. So I
 went back and she was still wandering about and it was. I didn't know my own grandma but I recognised the kind of - dog. So - that shows you I didn't know her very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents have friends, did they have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - there was
 this - Maggie Davison I keep telling you about who - mind she didn't - come very often, she'd been in service too but by then she - she was working in a grocers shop, she lived in Newcastle. But - maybe we went to their house once in a year and she would
 perhaps - come to ours twice in a year, but she usually came at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did they have any other friends you can think of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 They didn't have - particular friends, we were friendly enough people, well enough liked but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother have friends of her own, she had this Maggie Davison who was more her friend than your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Oh yes. But - my daddy like her, he used to - have fun with her, pull her leg you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Not - not that I would know about anyway, he might have had special friends at work or - but - not that came to the house, we weren't - given as much as most people I think to visiting back and forward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, but it - it was rather special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well I don't - well, it wasn't often at all, I don't know. Roughly maybe once in three months there would be somebody visit us - Sunday was th
e day, they couldn't just come whenever they felt like it, you know, it was come for Sunday tea. And then there might be - peaches out of a tin as a great treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink and was it on a special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, they were invited to a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well you see there weren't any, it was either relatives or it was Maggie Davison and I don't think anybody else ever came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did nobody else call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Very rarely. 'Cos - it was an old standing story mother had about - some man who - had come from Canada. I don't know what the connection was he, he must 
have known somebody that daddy knew who'd gone to Canada and he - he came and daddy just stood at the door, never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 even}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 invited him in, you see, that was as casual as our people were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did neighbours ever come in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, the - 
the Mrs Thompson for a period used to - come without a special invitation. No we - I don't know - maybe - we didn't have people in or - go into other people's houses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 They never went to visit neighbours but they went to visit relatives occasionally. And then we would be there as well probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with thei
r friends or neighbours, did they make music or play games? The only friend they'd get together with really was the friend of your mothers wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well our - our thing was cards that we used to play, we did - we didn't do music. Well - oh yes, oh 
yes, we were all roped in. And then sometimes were games like ludo and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who would be there then, which friends or neighbours would be there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - just daddy and mother and - Maggie. Oh she sometimes - brought her sister with her, an
 older sister called Mary, yes, that's coming out now. She had another sister called Phyllis but I don't remember her coming to the house. And - well of course the - dad's father didn't believe in cards so that - cards hadn't to be there when they came. B
ut - I think it must have been mostly among ourselves, just the four of us that we played these cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one class a
nd some to another? Could you tell me what the different ones were? Did you ever think of people belonging to different classes as a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well we thought we were as good as anybody else but nevertheless there - there were certain families we 
could tell that - they were better placed financially than we were. And - we could also tell that they - they thought themselves better than we were too. But - when - this first year at the - at the - the secondary school we scholarship kids were put in t
he two top classes, there were five classes altogether in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 first year}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
, and the people at the other end - were in the main better off, they were the people who were paying to go and better dressed and so on, but I have to say that we were the little snobs
 you know, we thought, oh we're - we are cleverer than you are, so that - we - we didn't - we didn't feel it as we might have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well we always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 reckoned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  to be working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you mean what were their jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, what were their jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't know, I think we - I don't think we would - discriminate at all. But - I think we - I think our family - h
ad a kind of feeling that in - in some ways we were superior to some other people, but we - we always - you know, we didn't drink and we didn't gamble and - we - we didn't buy on the never-never and - we didn't swear. So I suppose that's a kind of class s
t
rata in a way too. But - anybody who - wanted to talk to us, we - talked to them. Anybody who didn't want to we didn't, so you know, that was all right. Oh I still don't know what sort of people Well, the - the milkman and the - the shop assistants and th
e }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 railway men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 , miners. And the unemployed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of people would you say belonged to the other classes you've mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - oh yes. Well - I can think of people like - bank clerks, that - seemed to think they were above - I don't know, you 
know, I often didn't know what - what the men worked at anyway, or even if they were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Had you noticed or formed any opinion in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think I - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 dwelt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  on that kind of thing, it was more the - their clothes than anything
 else that seemed to make it a difference. And even that - I didn't probably become of aware of until I was about twelve or thirteen, when we were all little - we - we just accepted everybody and - seemed to accept us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When you were twelve or thirteen were you conscious that people had better clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - very - very much so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another, or did you treat everybody alike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh we - we treated 
- myself, I think I treated everybody alike in as far as I can tell - my parents did too, if I would come in and - tell mother something odd about - somebody else, you know, she would - laugh about it and - there was a kind of assumption that we knew bett
er than that but - nothing really strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Not really. Some of the classes at school we were all supposed to stand up if anybody - any visitor came into the room. That's not exa
ctly what you mean I don't think. Oh no, there was no curtseying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was there anyone you remembered calling sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh no. Were lucky if they sai
d, hi you. No, we - we didn't - in our family I think that there was a - slight - lack of courtesy, that we - didn't use peoples' names very much, some people, all the time they talking, Mr so and so and - and - and we never did, and - I sometimes feel my
 - in it's - feel it in myself now, that perhaps it's a lack in me that I don't - Mrs so and so all the time when I'm talking I - I don't normally used a name unless - it's necessary for that person to know whom it is - who it is I'm addressing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 In the district where you lived as a child who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
In the town? Oh - I don't know. Suppose the - the doctors loomed rather large and - we heard about councilors. Oh - there was a man called - Horn, who was a councillo
r. We - we used to celebrate Empire Day at school, at - in the - elementary school every year there was a bit of a do, and - paraded in the school yard and saluted the flag and so on, and some notability would - might come and talk to us. Well there was t
his Councillor Horn who had - he had a - rather big grocers shop on Sunderland Road, and - he was - regarded as being the big man of the area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you come into contact with the other important people, the doctor and the councilors? Apart from seeing Councillor Horn at school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't - I don't remember having any contact with anybody important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why do you think these people were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I - in - I - I'm - this isn't a tree I bark up when - the questions are not very r
elevant to me, we - we didn't - as children think of the important people of the town really. And - yes, quite but - I - I mean I - I can sort of - make something up and perhaps - exaggerate something but - it - it's honestly - doesn't come into it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you know who the shopkeepers in that area associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - well there - there was a - a shop, a very small shop, almost opposite us, next door to Mrs Thompson, a sweetshop, well they sold bread as well, I think they sold cakes - so - I don't k
now who else they would associate with but - you know, they were friendly enough with - with the other people. Oh they were - they were spiritualists, perhaps not all the time but - there was one phase when they were spiritualists. They - they weren't dif
f
erent from anybody else. There was - one boy called Tommy Temple who came to the - a little chapel afterwards who became an apprentice at the Co-op, so - he was in the football team and in the chapel and that was his media, he wasn't - wasn't any differen
t from anybody else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What about the clergy, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well I - I wouldn't know. Ministers used to come - occasionally to the house, he did come to the house about once in three months and I suppose he got a cup of tea when he 
came. But I don't know who their friends would be. The - the ministers - daughter - had a - a close friend who was - also went to the chapel but - not much help to you. I just don't know. It wasn't me anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What about the teachers, did you notice who they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, they - just among themselves mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever come into any contact with farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I'm - I just doesn't - I just wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who do you think employers associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well it - it just - n
ow that you're asking me it seems to me as though people mostly just associated with their own kind. But I - I - as a little girl I wouldn't know who - who were the friends of the - parsons and the doctors and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh - well there - there are - all sorts of people. Mind - the - there - there was a - a difference - in class, if we're going to use the word, between the - the two sets of the people, people at the two different chapels. There were -
 on the whole a better off crowd at the big chapel we went to first than at the small chapel that we - went to later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why was that, just because of the areas they were in or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - it would partly be, the - the big chapel was in a 
- a - a central point in Gateshead, you know where the - the Five Bridges Hotel is? Well it - that used to be Holy Corner with three chapels. And that was one of them. So it was a central point, and it - it probably had - people from a big area coming in 
t
o it. Whereas the other chapel was in a - a - an old - working class - rather going to ruin area that was between where we lived on this - outside estate, on the - the town centre, so they would draw on - clients from a smaller - and a more - more definit
ely - class area of people who were - poorer and doing - less well paid work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Was there any difference between the people who went to church and the people who went to chapel, did you ever notice the people who went to church, was there any difference in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No, not that I know of. You don't mean was there any difference between them? There was a - no, well I - this - this - you've made me think of something that's not quite the same, but - there was - a strong difference of feeling between the 
Protestants and Roman Catholic children at that time, yes. At this - well, they - be mostly the schoolchildren themselves, there were - there were the separate Roman Catholic schools and - they used to - well, bigger boys even used to have fights, they us
e
d to get into gangs, just - just because of the religion. There wasn't any real reason, it was just a kind of - pride and loyalty to their - their own, it was a very false thing I would say. And - there was a Roman Catholic family that - lived near to us 
and - they were all right, we got on all with - with them. They were a - bit - now then, a bit - come day, go day, a bit - careless, you know, improvident maybe but they were nice enough. They were Irish people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where you lived did all the people in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 working class}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups even within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 In - in my area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You hinted that there was a sort of difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, I - I don't think there would be a very big
 difference but there were - one or two - families - well there were one or two where there were only a husband and wife who were middle aged and - they would be better placed financially. And Mrs Thompson and her husband were better placed, they hadn't a
n
y children, he was a chemist. And - there was the family next door to us the other way with the four little girls and they also had - at least three sons who were older and - they seemed to be pretty poor. I - I think we were aware in a - kind of way that
 there were some - some differences, but we - we didn't - discriminate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you think that any one group felt itself superior to the rest, in the working class that is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Not that - not that really showed now, there might have done you see, I mean w
e - we weren't it, we - we were among the poorer ones. They might have felt superior and - they might - we might have felt that they showed it sometimes but I don't think it was very marked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, to some extent, yes, you could say the - the Natress' to - next door to us were a bit rough, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well - they - they spoke in a - in more rough way and - they - they were a bit more raggy in their c
lothing I suppose. And - I think the bigger boys used to stand around - the corner end rather about. I don't really know, they - they weren't - they weren't - literally rough but they - they were going around knocking people about. Yes, and this drunkenne
s
s bit would - come into it to some degree, not that that family had - I don't know of anything there. But - there was - it was much more important thing in - then whether people drank or not because - in the main father's could not afford to drink and - a
nd look after a family, and sometimes it got too much for them and they did drink. So then I suppose the families would become feckless as well and - it was a rough household.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers,
 was there any distinction between the craftsmen and the labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No, I never came across that until I was grown up really and I heard - wives any rather disparagingly of their husbands, he's only a labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, yes - yes, and that makes me thing maybe they were - they regarded themselves I think as being a bit exceptional that they didn't cow tow to anybody, so the implication is that other people must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well if she did - if she had thought about it she'd have accepted being working class
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Could this be because she was think of her parents or work or hou
se or your father, any particular reason why you think she'd think of herself as belonging to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - because, her - her own background was - working class at - her father had - been a worker and so she'd had to start work as soon a
s she left school and - and - well - you see - oh - I - I would include more people myself as being in the working class than perhaps - they would include themselves because if we - if we're workers we've got to have working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, can you remember anyone who did sort of move up the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well you can't do it in five minutes. But I've - I have a - a very strong and a - and close connection with the - the girl that I - did bec
ome my one single friend at the secondary school, who was even - worse off - a good deal worse off than we were. And - in time - she and - she and her husband - did - establish a - a very good and very well paying business, of course they're my age, they'
re retired now. But - you can't do it in five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 But it was possible then to work your way up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. There were these scholarships to - the second - I think an education had - had to - almost to be secured before you had got any sort of - entr\'e9e with employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady, and why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh that was a phrase my grandma Thorpe used to - use. The one at Ovingham. Yes. Any - pretty well anybody. Anybody th
at - she approved of. But - I just thought it was an old fashioned phrase that she used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You yourself never thought of anybody as being a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, no. No, it - it wasn't a way of thinking that we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Not a - he didn't come much round where we lived, but we - we used to see a policeman all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you think of him, when you were naughty did your mother ever any I'll call a policeman, were you at all frightened of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No. We weren't - but - it - it was a very coming thing for - for mothers to say at that time, a policeman, but - we thoroughly disapproved of - we knew even then - that it was silly that you should - teach chi
ldren to trust a policeman, turn to him for help rather than otherwise, not to be frightened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How do you think he treated the people in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Seemed to be fair enough. What funny questions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You say he was fair enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, he
 - I mean - there was - there was - there never - never any - anybody - finding fault with the way a policeman would behave, it was accepted that he - he did his job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I'
m not really sure, but - somebody called Mr Burns used to come - for the rent. I think it was every week. And I - I'm not sure whether he was the actual landlord or the agent. Well anyway there - there was bound to be some landlord and - I think - it was 
a
 good house, it really was - quite a good, they were - they were good houses in this place, it was - a strange sort of - group of houses. For the money it - it was a good house. I - I've never - I've no recollection of him being asked to do any work and r
efusing or anything of that sort. I think they were - pretty new houses and well built and I don't think they needed much attention.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle then to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, I - I do think that. I - 
I really - it must have been drummed into me when I was very little because it - it was - understood thing right through that - we couldn't have this and we couldn't have that and - we made do with - what was available.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you think about that, the fact that your parents had to struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I just accepted it, that was how it was, I - I'd have rather that - they had been able to be more - yes, well we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  - we would have liked it better if they - if they had been on more - things available, but - we weren't repining that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work, was he ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 He didn't have much - illness then and he was never out of work. And I - I think in his 
job there would have been - some money still to come if he was sick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there an
y special way they showed it? Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music, banging on pans and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. That's like - where the expression comes from, drummed 'em out? Yes, so did I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I think I would be five, I don't really know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It was - nine 'til twelve and half past one until four. Oh of course when we were in the - infants it would be half past three likely.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you do a full day straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What kind of a school was it, your first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - the very first one I went was in Newcastle you know and you asked me to concentrate more on the - the Gateshead one. So
 - what - what Have I to say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 The first one you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, but I've forgotten the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - oh no, it was what you - we - they called a board school but I think that was - think that was out of da
te then. Everybody called it a board school. It was a big school and - it - must have been fairly newly built. It's still there, Westgate Hill School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was it for boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think so, but the - the infants were mixed. I don't think the - for the older boys and girls it would be mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you get to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh it was very close, I - just walked, it was - we - our front door faced onto the - the - what would be the back wall of the school yard. Wasn't far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No - I don't remember every - anybody going with me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What happened about your midday meal at that first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh we went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you think of that first school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I was only there a few months but - I had a - I think - there was a friendly enough nice enough atmosphere, I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember if the teachers emphasised certain things as important in life at that first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Manners, punctuality, tidiness or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember what would happen at that first school if you did something the teachers disapproved of, ho
w did they punish the children, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No - I - I was only - I think I must only have been there probably about - eight months, and that would likely be in the baby class. I can the - remember the classroom, they had a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3214789\charrsid15804465 swing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  and a rocking horse. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Do you remember your parents showing an interest in your schoolwork in those early days, did they ask you what you did at school or visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I don't think so, but when - when my brother start
ed school they - they did ask him what he'd learnt when he first went and so on so they would probably do the same with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember if the other children came from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I expect so. There - there was 
one - one little boy with - with long hair, I can remember two or three of us - pushing him into the girls line and - a poor little girl whose hair had been shaved putting him into - her in to the boy lines. You know - there used to be a lot of what they 
called fever in those days, they used to take all the hair off the girls heads, there was nearly always one girl in a class whose head had been shaved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember if the teachers singled out some children for different treatment from the others at that first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. Well really I - I think I've told you all I can remember about that, the incident in the lines and about the classroom with the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any gangs or groups in the school and were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I've no idea, I don't think so, I just feel - happy about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did you go to next then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 This was Shipcote infants school in Gateshead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You were still about five then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I was less than five. I'm sorry, I mean I was less than six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What time did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 The same times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What kind of a school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well it was the infants department and there - there were two separate - schools for boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was this a board school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you get to school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 We walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well as far as I know I always went myself. Later on I took my brother of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh we used to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you think of this school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you feel about the teachers here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you stay all the time there until you went to the secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners or tidiness, do you remember anything they told you about manners or tidiness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How are you taking right up to - the whole period, the - the infants and the girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Oh I - I think probably - they were rather - rather hot on - not just - manners but - moral teaching including manners, being - being decent to other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't really think they did. You see, we - were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 heterogeneous}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
 lot - with - father's unemployed or - or poor in the main and - and - I don't think they could have done much about us - they had to accept us as - as we were, it wasn't - if there was anything wrong with us it wasn't -
 it wasn't our fault, it was the parents and there weren't any parent teacher associations, there wasn't that contact, and the classes were so big. In - in the girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  school there were sixty in a class. There wouldn't be so many in the infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What about punctuality, were they keen on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh yes, yes. They used - there used to be the strap for people who were late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What about ways of speaking, did they help to improve the speech at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 I don't think they consciously did any - speech training, as such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen, you said they got the cane for being late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, the strap it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Any other means of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well - any - it - it was possible to be kept in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the girls get the same punishment as the boys do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Well - we weren't in the same building. I think probably the boys would be able to be caned. We were - in the same building but they had the downstairs and we had the upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 For what sort of offences, you said for being late, can you remember any other offences people getting the strap for or being kept in for?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - as - untidiness comes into this if - they made blots and so on their work they - they could be 
- kept in or - or even strapped. A lot depended on - on the individual teacher. Some - some had the name of being - crabby, you know, ready with the strap and others - didn't have to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork here do you remember, when you were getting a bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well to me they didn't seem to show very much interest. They might have been more interested than I realized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you ever remember them visiting the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Not - not until later on and - it was 
one time when mother came to my rescue. The war keeps colouring this and after a while we had to - leave that school to be occupied by soldiers, and we went to - half time to another school called South Street and we did - either did a long - morning or a
 
long afternoon. Then that changed again and - I don't know how many of us, but some of us anyway - went to - the Education Office at Sutton and had - had the school there. Well the headmistress was going to take a lesson this time and they - they had - sh
e
 had this way of moving us along - in the desks, instead of sitting two in a desk when she was going to talk to us she would have us - three in a desk but - this occasionally four in a desk. And - she - she told us to - to move along three in a desk so we
 were moving along and we were three in a desk and another girl was trying to - come in and I was saying, it's three in a desk. And - this headmistress came and slapped my face. And - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was this still at Shipcote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 It was - it was called Shipco
te school, yes. And - the odd time I'd - had little bits of trouble I suppose. And - it - it was such a smack that it showed when I got home, I suppose I - I was concerned because - I - you know, I thought it was a bit much, I was trying to interpret her 
instructions really, I wasn't just talking. So this time mother would go and see about it which was - you know, oh was going to be marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 ous. But - I didn't get much change out of it, she got there and the - Miss Lisle the headmistress was all friendly and
 showing her all round and so on you know. Mother told other people about it, when she went - how she - she'd gone in war and she'd come back in - peace you know and she'd had practically had the teacher eating out of her hand she thought and - and I, you
 know, I thought well you know this doesn't get me anywhere, I was supposed to be - going to have some sort of - retribution for this -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the other children at this school come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. There again, th
ere would - there would be the odd one that was - better dressed and - although there were some that - a few that were quite pampered, their mother would - come at playtime and give them cakes and sweets and so on you know. But - we weren't jealous of tha
t kind of thing, we - we - you know, we didn't agree with it, we thought it was - classified. But - in the main we were all the same kind of people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I - I do
n't quite know what you mean by that, it wouldn't be according to their class. It would be - according to - their ability and how well they worked like they - they always had some monitors whose - it was normally the people who were at the top of the clas
s
 after examinations and - and they were - picked to - to help with giving books out and pencils out and ink and - tidying the cupboards sometimes cleaning the blackboard, so - that seemed to me to - to work fair enough, especially as I was generally one o
f the monitors. But - if - if you call that singling people out they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well if - if you're implying were there rough groups - no, I wouldn't think so. People - they did get into some sort of clique
s naturally to some extent you stuck to your own little crowd. But there - there was nothing - unsavoury at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - you know - it seems to me that in - pretty well every class there - ther
e seemed to be one or two - odd ones because of their disability. There was - there was often - what we called a dummy, somebody who was deaf and therefore couldn't talk either and - there was sometimes what we called a dafty, somebody who - oughtn't to h
ave been - mixed in with the other ones as well. And - well in the nature of things to some extent they would be on their own, you know, we - we didn't adopt them and pal up with them, I don't know what happened to them at playtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You won a scholarship and you went to the secondary school, would you be eleven then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I was twelve in July and started in the - September you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So we've got a couple of years to ask you about there haven't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well nearly, yes. Eighteen months if you're going stick strictly to - December 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 So what kind of hours did you do, the same sort of hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Was it just for girls or was it mixed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No it was mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you get to this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh still walked, it was a bit further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How long would it take you do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh not very long, twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you still go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh - I used to - meet my friend usually by then and she was so far on the way and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh, came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What did you think of the secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you feel about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - most of them I liked all right, the - they varied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did those teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, manners, tidiness, punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No. Mostly what they emphasised was working hard and - getting on well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 In the early days of the secondary school if you did something the teachers disapprov
ed of what would happen, how did they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh there were lines or - detention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 For what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - not always but periodically there used to be a - a - an onslaught on punctuality and people who'd - appeared mor
e than once in the late - line over a period of - they were due for some sort of - punishment, generally detention, which - I mean, that - that is pretty apt isn't it, if you come late you stay late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the girls get the same punishment as the boys here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No, the boys could get the cane but the girls didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the girls never get the cane at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No. No. I don't think it was allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork here, were they proud of you getting a scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I - yes, at the time daddy particularly. I think it was a surprise, they didn't - at the school as well even, they didn't - there were three of us suddenly - got these scholarships and it had never - they hadn't attempted it for
 years, they'd not - never put anybody in to sit. Oh yes. They never expected that - anybody from there - their school - would be any good you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How many of you got through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Three - they put three of us in and we all got through. And - I thi
nk - looking back I think it was a bit of a - a revelation, both at school and - in the neighbourhood that the ordinary people like us could go there. So that - and - I got a tennis racquet to go - of course you had - pretty well had to get a tennis racqu
et. But - it was - this cost twelve and six and you could get them for seven and six so that - that showed something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did your parents ask you what you did at the secondary school? Did they ever visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Don't think
 they ever did. And - the headmaster - happened to have been a teacher of my father's when they were at Sunderland. So I - and yet I don't think they ever made the effort to meet him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not, they'd be very mixed wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes. Well I touched on that in another connection that they - they - they were on - on the whole a - a lot more - better off children than we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did the teachers single out any children for different treatment from the others at the secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No, no. It's difficult to know what this question is getting at. Well it - it sounds as though they're wondering whether - whether the - the better off children got better treatment or something li
ke that, but - there wasn't - there wasn't that kind of discrimination ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Do you remember any gangs or groups in this school? Or any children who were left out of things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 There was - yes, just - there was one girl in our class who - I can't 
understand how it came about but she was a bit older than the rest of us. I don't know why that should be, you see, there was an age limit for this - I can't understand that - how that could be, but - and she was a Jewess and she had - a cousin in the sch
o
ol, in another class, and they - when they weren't in class they kept together fairly well but once - once she was in our class, although - she was a nice girl, so now we didn't think about including her. And when it came to - splitting ourselves up as we
 
were told to do into - regular fours who would - be allowed to play tennis in the evening for evening games, she was the last one - by then there were three of us, the friends, the three of us who'd gone - from Shipcote to the secondary together we were f
riends and she came to us, but you know, we didn't sort of look round and say, who - is there an odd one to join us, she was the one that was left and - sort of came on sufferance to some extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Were there any gangs or groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 No, I - no, I don't think there was anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 You stayed at that school until you were seventeen did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, practically - practically seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
It wasn't allowed in those days, not even when I went to college, it - that was part of - what had to be signed before we went, that we mustn't on any account do any paid work and we must not on any account do any housework in the home, an
d that - that part didn't work out, but that was - that was what you had to sign.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What jobs have you done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
Yes, well - I haven't done any other paid work except teaching. And a bit of part time education secretary that - that used to be. But it's something similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Would you have preferred another type of occupation or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 What would you have liked to have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well I used to say I would have liked to be a King's mistress but - I hear they used to have a n
ice time - and be the power behind the throne. No, I - I think an organising job like - a personal secretary or something like that would have suited me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period, you went to college, how many years were you at college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you belong to any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 trade union}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  or professional }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 organization}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Well - afterwards? Well we were invited to join the N.U.T. in the last year and - we did as - I've forgotten the expression.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you take part in any of it's activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. Was on the committee. I was - there was also the Class Teachers Association that I joined almost straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you take part in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Yes. And I came a chairman of that at the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Oh well in - in my job of course they did - pretty well have the same interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 Did you feel there were divisions of interest among workers and would you say that full time work c
hanged your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
No. But it - it changed - harking back to my mother, it changed her attitude to me when - when I brought some money in. Well I was the same person and I wasn't working any harder but when I brought some money in - then I - was treated differently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11298321 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 How did you feel about - how did she accept the fact that you were clever enough to carry on, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3875373\charrsid15804465 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465  she proud of you then, did she accept that, you said earlier she expected you to go in for domestic service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14840838 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2044917\charrsid15804465 
I don't know, she - she didn't show pride in me. I think - I think daddy must have swanked at work a bit about me though from - something. I - I know - I don't know - she - I don't - she just seemed to, I suppose, take it as it came. But see in he
r day there - there wasn't anything else really except domestic service for people. And in - in my time there wasn't - an awful lot of - of - decent work for young women you know. We were pushed into this - teaching lark when we were only - thirteen. Yes,
 
we were offered - a - a sort of grant - on condition that we - would become teachers in due course. It wasn't very much, I think it was - perhaps ten pounds for two years or something. Then in the sixth form you could become what they called a probationer
. No, it wasn't as much as that, I think it must have been two five pounds and then ten pounds. And - that was supposed to - be all cut and dried, that you were going to train for teaching.
\par }}